      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM BIG BUSINESS (5) carried on his good form from Victoria when he led to get home by 5.4m here last week. That took his record at this circuit and distance to two wins and a placing from three attempts. Draws wider but is going well enough to overcome that and strike again. HAWKESDALE DEED (4) was a class above in her latest appearance at Mt Gambier, leading and cruising home by more than 13m. Draws deeper but came from wider than this to score at Ouyen prior so could land the hat trick. CENTREFOLD STAR (1) is back from a spell of three-and-a-half months after finishing the last campaign with a string of seconds, the last two from this draw. Won her lone fresh attempt and was readied with a trial. DELIGHTFUL DREAM (6) draws wider but has looked good in easily winning his two starts at this circuit and distance off a spell so must be respected.",
